parameters: Thief Nora: I, I woke up!

Iron Mask: Wh-where is this... ugh... my head...
hurts...

Clea: I received a search request from your son. Please
tell me why you were fighting in the underground arena.

Guard Cleos: After my infiltration was discovered, I was
forced to wear this armor and made to fight as a spectacle
in the underground arena.

Guard Cleos: I was consumed by hatred... for a long, long
time... I was completely devoted to swinging my sword and
defeating my enemies.

Priestess Sophia: Armor infused with curses... It's
incredibly dangerous, isn't it?

Priestess Phoni: Please leave this armor to me. I believe
that if I work together with your father, we can neutralize
it.

Guard Cleos: I've decided to withdraw from the underground
arena. Those who possess such armor are beyond my personal
capabilities to handle.

Guard Cleos: I want you all to be careful. This city,
Dromos, is swirling with desires and violence.

Guard Cleos: Thank you for saving me. I'm so happy to be
alive and able to see my son again more than anything.

Mage Relm: You figured out the true identity of the Iron
Mask well, didn't you?

Clea: At the end of the battle, I heard a small voice
saying thank you.
Clea: But I still had a feeling that maybe...
Thief Nora: Who was the person wearing the armor?

Priestess Sophia: Let's not get too involved either. There
are things in this world that it's better not to know.
Clea: Let's escort Cleos-san to Oros.
